      "摘要": "This paper proposes SYNCHECK, a lightweight monitor that leverages fine-grained decoding dynamics to synchronously detect unfaithful sentences in retrieval-augmented language models (RALMs). It also introduces FOD, a faithfulness-oriented decoding algorithm guided by beam search for long-form retrieval-augmented generation. Empirical results show that SYNCHECK outperforms prior methods in detecting faithfulness errors, and FOD significantly improves the faithfulness of generated outputs across multiple datasets.",
